Discussed with PS. They use the request notes per transaction for staff use. Lets roll it out in the current model where it applies to every TN in the cart. (We might have to come back to this and have it apply to each transaction separately/possibly offer the option to apply to all or just one?) Can those options be investigated in the meantime?

The only other thing to roll this out in production would be to add a explanation/description to the note. Maybe a hover over bubble?

@ccleeton Hover bubbles don't work for mobile users, but maybe we can keep it short and keep it in the input field hint. What would the explanation/description say? Something like "Notes to Special Collections staff"?
The sense I got was that we want users to know it will apply to all things in the cart. But I like the notes to staff part.

pulfalight.title: Credit this material note displaying old template in addition to correct info
Display full location information for oversize items on record page (cabinet, drawer, folder)

comments.body:
Public Services discussed this in our meeting today. We have a few staff related reasons we would want the top container notes to display in the finding aid. We discussed the security concerns and have felt they are not an issue. Mainly we write the location on the call slips, the locations don't mean anything to the regular user. Public Maps do not display zone information.
@faithc Could you bring this to ADAPT and make sure you all agree.

Thanks, @ccleeton. This may already be known, but the issue is that location info that had previously been public (like folder, cabinet, etc.) as well as location info that had been internal (like compartment letters and sections within compartments)--the data were in separate sections of EADs-- were both added to the same notes field in ASpace since that is seemingly the only place these text notes could go. I'll check in with ADAPT, but if PS is ok with this info displaying on the site, then it's probably fine? One question: you mention that staff write the location on call slips. All of this info will be automatically routed to Aeon/call slips, right?
